TEXT 112 1080 Left 2 ;How to Control This (The Ultimate Single-Stage Strategy)\nIn a real, high-end Single-Stage LLC, the DSP (Digital Controller) uses a Hybrid Control Strategy:\nAt the Peak of the AC Sine Wave (High Voltage):\nThe secondary MOSFETs act exactly like normal diodes (Synchronous Rectification). The primary bridge uses PFM (Frequency Control) to shape the current, exactly like we did in the LTspice equations earlier.\nAt the Zero-Crossings of the AC Sine Wave (Low Voltage):\nThe primary bridge stops changing frequency and locks to a fixed frequency. The secondary MOSFETs switch to PWM (Pulse Width Modulation) Control. They intentionally short-circuit the secondary winding for microseconds at a time to "boost" the tiny AC voltage up to the 48V output.
